iSIGN MEDIA SOLUTIONS INC



 



Opportunity Stocks Daily Picks




 I
			SIGN MEDIA
                SOLUTIONS INC.
  
 ISDSF - OTC $0.13 US / TSX-V ISD 
			$0.16 CDN
  
 Strong Buy -Target $0.40  
			/ Watch CEO Interviews At Bottom Of Report  

 




Overview 

As a result of  the June 
					22nd, 2016 Priority Post announcement on iSIGN's web site 
					regarding E Health Consortium Group and the installation 
					of  350-500 Smart Antennas  in 35 hospitals in the State 
					of Victoria in Australia and the roll-out into the remaining 
					7 States of up to 4000 Smart Antennas  going forward, we 
					have decided to raise iSIGN's target price to $1.00 per 
					share. Once all installations are completed in every one of 
					Australia's hospitals and connected with iSIGN's security 
					device and other big data components we expect that the 
					company’s revenues will exceed 5 million dollars annually 
					from this one client.  iSIGN earns 60-70 % of all revenues, 
					due to the nature of its recurring monthly fees for data 
					management and message broadcasting against which there is 
					little cost.

iSIGN Media Solutions  is on the 
					verge of major revenue streams from different industries 
					such as shopping complexes/amusement parks and airports. It 
					is our belief that iSIGN's licensing agreement with Rich 
					Multimedia Technologies that call for 8600 Smart Antennas to 
					be integrated into their phone kiosks for installation 
					in Mexico and major airports throughout North Americas will, 
					on its own, bring about profitability to the Company.

Recently, a major North 
					American insurance company has categorized the smart antenna 
					as a safety and security device which will open new markets 
					for iSIGN especially 
					in amusement centers, malls and commercial real estate 
					projects. 

We believe with all these new and 
					exciting developments  with iSIGN's proprietary and 
					patented technology,  the stock is a very attractive 
					speculation and could trade up to $1.00 
					per share before the end of 2016. 

eHealth Consortium Group in 
					Australia Update  / June 22, 2016


					According to our reseller, JEA Technologies, eHealth 
					Consortium Group's intention is to start installations in 
					hospitals located in the State of Victoria.  
					Installations into hospitals located in the States of New 
					South Wales, Queensland, Northern Territory, Western 
					Australia, South Australia, Tasmania and Australian Capital 
					Territory would follow later.

As advised by JEA, the State of 
					Victoria has a population of 4.6 million people and has 24 
					major government owned and operated hospitals in the 
					Melbourne Metropolitan area, as well as 11 private hospital 
					corporations.

The projected number of Smart 
					Antennas per hospital, ranges from 10 to 15, which will be 
					determined once site surveys at each hospital are completed.  
					Installations are expected to be in:  (i) each public 
					entrance, installed into the entrance's digital signage or 
					the hospital way finding kiosks (information systems that 
					guide people through a physical environment and enhance 
					their understanding and experience of the space); (ii) the 
					public food courts of the hospital's cafeteria areas; 
					(iii) the Accident & Emergency departments where there are 
					long waiting times; and (iv) public waiting areas.

The total number of Smart 
					Antennas for the 35 hospitals in the State of Victoria is 
					expected to be from a minimum of 350 to a maximum of 525 for 
					these hospitals and would increase as installations expand 
					into the other 7 States.  iSIGN revenues will be 
					derived from the sale of the Smart Antenna units as well 
					as the monthly data management/message broadcasting fees. 

Our technology and Smart Antennas 
					are being promoted to architects who are responsible for 
					interior design and hardware supply, such as digital LCD 
					signage, way finders, etc.  In the  State of 
					Victoria, the process is to work through level 1 and level 2 
					specifications and tender processes for government hospital 
					supply and system integrations.  Each hospital may have 
					different levels of procurement and capex rules, needs and 
					requirements.  

Contract length is expected to 
					vary per hospital and will range from 24 to 36 months, with 
					each contract to be renewable at the end of the initial 
					period.

The following is the list of the 
					24 government owned public hospitals in the State of 
					Victoria:


Austin Health (http://www.austin.org.au/); 
Austin Health - Austin Hospital (http://www.austin.org.au/austin-hospital); 
Austin Health - Heidelberg 
					Repatriation Hospital (http://www.austin.org.au/heidelberg-repatriation-hospital); 
Box Hill Hospital (http://www.easternhealth.org.au/locations/boxhill/default.aspx); 
Casey Hospital (http://www.monashhealth.org/page/Hospitals/Caseyhospital/); 
Dandenong Hospital (https://www.monashhealth.org/page/Hospitals/Dandenong/); 
Dental Health Services Victoria (http://www.dhsv.org.au/); 
Eastern Health (http://www.easternhealth.org. 
					au/); 
Frankston Hospital (http://www.peninsulahealth. org.au/locations/frankston/); 
Maroondah Hospital (http://www.easternhealth.org.au/Locations/Maroondah/default.aspx); 
Melbourne Health (http://www.thermh.org.au/);
Mercy Hospital for Women (http://www.mercyhealth.com.au/); 
Mercy Public Hospitals Inc. (http://www.mercy.com.au/); 
Monash Health (http://www.monashhealth.org/); 
Northern Health (http://www.nh.org.au/); 
Peter MacCallum Cancer Institute 
					(http://www.petermac.org/); 
